# Prettier scope: intentional source and docs only. Everything below is generated,
# vendored, or machine-managed — formatting it is noise (and would fight the tools
# that own it). node_modules is ignored by Prettier automatically.

# Build / compiled output
dist/
lib/
functions/lib/
*.tsbuildinfo

# Test / coverage / tooling output
coverage/
functions/coverage/
playwright-report/
test-results/
blob-report/
.playwright-browsers/

# Machine-managed lockfiles
package-lock.json
functions/package-lock.json

# Local, per-developer settings (not a shared source doc)
**/settings.local.json

# Markdown docs are reviewed as prose, and several (AGENTS.md, .claude/rules/*) carry
# wide hand-maintained reference tables that Prettier's column-alignment reflows into
# unwieldy 300-char lines — re-padded on every row add. Keep docs out of the formatter.
*.md

